  <revision rev="3" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>f5d07f9cd65805bb11f79d340e8bd18d</srcmd5>
    <version>1.8.4</version>
    <time>1784406309</time>
    <user>dimstar_suse</user>
    <comment>Update to 1.8.4.

Security: CVE-2026-35469 (bsc#1262264) — resource exhaustion in the
vendored moby/spdystream SPDY/3 implementation, fixed by the upstream
v0.5.0 -&gt; v0.5.1 bump.

Also from upstream 1.8.4: node-labeller uses the new libvirt
feature-expansion flags; fix a gRPC connection leak in
GetLauncherClient and clean up the ghost launcher record on connection
setup failure; validate VMI VSOCK CID and checksum status fields as
uint32; virt-operator canary-flow refinement for out-of-band changes;
new virt-api/virt-handler/virt-operator ready/down metrics, alerts and
recording rules. disks-images-provider.yaml refreshed to the v1.8.4
image tag.

Validated with a full sig-compute e2e run against this build
(915 specs, 717 passed, 3 known environmental flakes).</comment>
    <requestid>1366526</requestid>
  </revision>
  <revision rev="4" vrev="2">
    <srcmd5>13d9567dddcfbc1a623f5bceb33410fe</srcmd5>
    <version>1.8.4</version>
